    "In his own time <a href=\"/bellorig\">Giovanni Pietro Bellori</a> used Baglione's <em>Vite</em> for his book <em>Le vite de' pittori, scultori et architetti moderni</em> of 1672, though Bellori was jealous of Baglione's authority accused him of having the work ghostwritten by the antiquarian Ottavio Tronsarelli (d.": [],
    "1646).": [],
    "Others using Baglione included <a href=\"/malvasiac\">Carlo Cesare Malvasia</a> for his biographies published beginning in 1678, <a href=\"/passerig\">Giovanni Battista Passeri</a> for his work of 1678 and in Spain, <a href=\"/palominoa\">Acisclo Antonio Palomino de Castro y Velasco</a> in his <em>Museo pict\u00f3rico y escala \u00f3ptica</em>, 1715-1724.": [
