    "His work became an important source for modern art historians studying his age, including <a href=\"/lanzil\">Luigi Antonio Lanzi</a>, <a href=\"/baruffaldig\">Girolamo Cluento Nettunio Baruffaldi</a>, <a href=\"/vossh\">Hermann Voss</a>, <a href=\"/hessj\">Jacob Hess</a> and <a href=\"/blunta\">Anthony Blunt</a>.": [],
    "The importance of his work is testified by the fact that a separate index to it appeared in 1924 (Rome), a facsimile edition in 1935 (also Rome), and Hess' commentary in 1995.": []
